Dad?

25
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:47,260
Hey, Jae-in.

26
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:50,760
What's up? Can't you sleep?

27
00:03:51,090 --> 00:03:52,730
Well...

28
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:55,930
Can I sit down for a second?

29
00:03:56,230 --> 00:03:58,530
I want to hang out with you.

30
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:00,540
Sure.

31
00:04:16,579 --> 00:04:18,690
What's that? A family picture?

32
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:19,750
What?

33
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:28,000
Mr. Oh, I have a question.

34
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:31,430
Can my dad be my friend's dad too?

35
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:35,640
Can your dad be your friend's dad?

36
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,010
What do you mean?

37
00:04:40,710 --> 00:04:42,140
Well...

38
00:04:44,010 --> 00:04:46,710
On my dad's phone, Yi-chan...

39
00:04:49,620 --> 00:04:50,990
Never mind.

40
00:04:53,150 --> 00:04:56,060
What about your dad? Is something wrong?

41
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:59,560
I haven't seen him in ages.

42
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:02,200
I miss him.

43
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:07,670
But when I ask my mom,
she never answers and just becomes sad.

44
00:05:08,340 --> 00:05:11,070
Oh, I see.

45
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:19,480
You know what?

46
00:05:20,450 --> 00:05:23,580
I don't have a dad.

47
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,490
I don't have a mom either.

48
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:28,520
Are you an orphan?

49
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,530
Yes, I am.

50
00:05:31,260 --> 00:05:33,590
Or maybe not, because I'm a grown-up now.

51
00:05:33,659 --> 00:05:35,530
Don't you miss them?

52
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,100
I do.

53
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:39,600
Every single day.

54
00:05:39,670 --> 00:05:41,740
Then what do you do?

55
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,140
It's a secret. Do you want to know?

56
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:51,080
Before going to bed,
I put my hands over my heart

57
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:53,450
and look up at the sky.

58
00:05:54,150 --> 00:05:57,950
And I think of the happiest moments
I had with my parents.

59
00:05:58,290 --> 00:06:01,260
Then I can see them in my dream.

60
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:05,460
You're lying. That doesn't make sense.

61
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:06,960
It's true.

62
00:06:07,030 --> 00:06:09,760
Try it when you can't sleep. You'll see.

63
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:59,110
When did she come here?
I've been looking everywhere for her.

64
00:06:59,180 --> 00:07:01,120
About an hour ago.

65
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,980
She just fell asleep.

66
00:07:03,350 --> 00:07:04,820
I'll bring her to the tent later.

67
00:07:04,890 --> 00:07:06,890
No. I'll take her now.

68
00:07:12,490 --> 00:07:13,530
Jae-in.

69
00:07:14,860 --> 00:07:16,430
Jae-in, wake up.

70
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:18,700
Jae-in.

71
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:20,770
Goodness.

72
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:27,010
Thank you, Danny.

73
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:29,480
I'll make it up to you sometime soon.

74
00:07:29,540 --> 00:07:30,610
Sure.

75
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,430
-Sweetheart.
-Yes?

76
00:07:51,570 --> 00:07:52,670
I love you.

77
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:02,180
One more time?

78
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,110
Will you be okay?

79
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:09,920
-I'll go take a shower.
-What?

80
00:08:09,980 --> 00:08:11,020
Gosh.

81
00:08:58,970 --> 00:09:00,030
My goodness.

82
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:02,600
That scared me.

83
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:10,680
-Hello?
[-Hello, this is Rachel.]

84
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:13,410
[I'm so sorry, but Si-woo...]

85
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,280
Is he throwing another tantrum?

86
00:09:15,350 --> 00:09:17,850
[Mom, I want to go home.]

87
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:20,960
Si-woo, don't be like that.

88
00:09:21,020 --> 00:09:23,960
[I don't care! I want to go home!]

89
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:28,000
[Come pick me up right now! Hurry!]

90
00:09:31,830 --> 00:09:33,370
That little brat.

91
00:09:39,010 --> 00:09:40,840
Sweetie, do you want more wine?

92
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:43,540
No. I have to go. My kid is asking for me.

93
00:09:46,850 --> 00:09:49,520
Then you should go.
You have clear priorities.

94
00:09:49,780 --> 00:09:53,190
What do you expect me to do?
Forget about the kid

95
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,990
and stay with you?

96
00:09:59,730 --> 00:10:00,760
There you go.

97
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,600
Thank you. I'm off. Bye.

98
00:10:05,570 --> 00:10:07,270
By the way,

99
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,910
don't come out right away, okay?

100
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,910
Order another bottle of wine
and charge it to the room.

101
00:10:14,910 --> 00:10:15,980
All right.

102
00:10:27,190 --> 00:10:29,890
Can you charge my...

103
00:10:29,990 --> 00:10:33,230
-What?
-You know...

104
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:38,370
Gosh, look at him falling asleep
as soon as we got in the car.

105
00:10:43,540 --> 00:10:45,340
Can you...

106
00:10:49,010 --> 00:10:51,850
[Chef Jung Mi-do]

107
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:03,220
[The person you have reached
is not available.]

108
00:11:02,890 --> 00:11:05,160
[Chef Jung Mi-do]

109
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:17,570
When did you come out here?

110
00:11:19,510 --> 00:11:20,940
I couldn't sleep.

111
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:25,150
What a gorgeous day.

112
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,920
This breeze and the smell of the sea.

113
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:30,790
Murky clouds can rush across the sky
all of a sudden

114
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:32,390
and bring a torrential downpour.

115
00:11:32,490 --> 00:11:35,020
Really? But it's so sunny right now.

116
00:11:37,690 --> 00:11:39,790
The weather here is like

117
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:41,460
a woman you can't figure out.

118
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:45,900
Never let your guard down.

119
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,640
You never know when it'll turn nasty.

120
00:11:51,770 --> 00:11:53,510
I guess you're really sensitive too.

121
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,810
It looks like you barely slept last night.

122
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,550
It happens once in a while.

123
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:03,120
I get it. Before I moved here,

124
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,650
I couldn't sleep without my sleeping pills
for a while.

125
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:07,720
Are you still like that?

126
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:09,820
Some days, I don't even think of it.

127
00:12:11,830 --> 00:12:14,900
I'm sure I'll forget all about it
with time.

128
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,730
I just can't imagine.

129
00:12:18,930 --> 00:12:20,300
How could something like that happen?

130
00:12:22,140 --> 00:12:23,470
I felt just the same.

131
00:12:32,810 --> 00:12:33,880
Honey.

132
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,350
Yes, hold on.

133
00:12:39,450 --> 00:12:42,360
It's a fund, so it's safe.
Trust me and just wait.

134
00:12:44,230 --> 00:12:45,790
Have you ever seen me go back on my word?

135
00:12:45,990 --> 00:12:47,160
Don't worry.

136
00:12:48,630 --> 00:12:49,760
That's right.

137
00:12:52,130 --> 00:12:55,100
[Something was going wrong.]

138
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:58,270
I'll tell you everything
when the time is right.

139
00:12:59,370 --> 00:13:00,640
So for now,

140
00:13:02,010 --> 00:13:03,740
please just trust me and wait.

141
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:10,180
You trust me, don't you?

142
00:13:13,190 --> 00:13:15,090
[I should've asked more questions then,]

143
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,590
[but I couldn't.]

144
00:13:18,490 --> 00:13:20,230
He told me to trust him,

145
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,100
and I wanted to believe him.

146
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:28,100
Then when I woke up, he was already gone.

147
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,270
Is that it?

148
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:35,740
I wonder why he made such a choice,

149
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,510
and why he didn't tell me anything.

150
00:13:39,550 --> 00:13:41,850
Although, I'm sure there was a reason
he couldn't tell me.

151
00:13:48,020 --> 00:13:50,490
Anyway, I must go on living.

152
00:13:51,460 --> 00:13:53,330
He may be gone,

153
00:13:54,530 --> 00:13:55,830
but I have Yi-chan.

154
00:14:01,140 --> 00:14:02,670
This is a boring topic.

155
00:14:02,970 --> 00:14:04,610
Let's go get some breakfast.

156
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,570
Sounds good.

157
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:22,920
[Closed on Wednesdays]

158
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:20,720
-Shall we eat here?
-Sure.

159
00:14:22,290 --> 00:14:23,860
Hello!

160
00:14:23,990 --> 00:14:25,660
-Come on in.
-Thank you.

161
00:14:26,590 --> 00:14:28,460
[Murex porridge, Takeout available]

162
00:14:28,530 --> 00:14:33,770
[Hijiki octopus pancakes, Makgeolli]

163
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:31,470
Look. Isn't she that woman?

164
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:34,470
The woman who recently moved
to your neighborhood.

165
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:37,300
Her husband took his own life, right?

166
00:14:37,610 --> 00:14:38,640
Who?

167
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:41,740
-This one, right?
-Quiet down. She'll hear you.

168
00:14:41,710 --> 00:14:44,980
[Rinse off the sand by the restroom.]

169
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:45,710
Excuse me.

170
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:49,050
My gosh, sir.

171
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:52,750
Hello. I didn't know it was you.

172
00:14:52,890 --> 00:14:55,320
Are you all unpacked and settled in now?

173
00:14:55,390 --> 00:14:57,890
[Takeout available]

174
00:14:59,230 --> 00:15:01,600
-Let's eat somewhere else.
-Okay.

175
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:08,040
Look at her acting like nothing's wrong
after her husband died.

176
00:15:09,570 --> 00:15:12,440
Ma'am. What did you just say?

177
00:15:12,910 --> 00:15:16,110
What? Why do you care what others say?

178
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:18,210
I just stated a fact.

179
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:21,420
If you have a question,
you can ask me directly.

180
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:23,320
Don't talk behind my back.

181
00:15:23,450 --> 00:15:27,490
You need better manners
when you run a restaurant.

182
00:15:28,290 --> 00:15:29,360
What?

183
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:32,730
How dare you talk to me like that?

184
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:35,530
Ma'am, please calm down.

185
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,370
Yeo-wool.

186
00:15:37,830 --> 00:15:41,670
[Takeout available]

187
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:44,910
Today, there's a lot of...

188
00:15:48,180 --> 00:15:51,710
My gosh. What are you doing here?

189
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,150
Yeo-wool, let's go.

190
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:56,820
There's a good rockfish soup place nearby.

191
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:58,120
Let's go there.

192
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,400
You know who she is, right?

193
00:16:08,460 --> 00:16:11,370
-The new resident in--
-I have to go to work.

194
00:16:11,430 --> 00:16:13,130
-Pay me for these.
-Okay.

195
00:16:20,570 --> 00:16:23,680
I'm sorry I made things awkward
for you too.

196
00:16:24,010 --> 00:16:28,180
No, it's okay.
The locals here aren't nice to outsiders.

197
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:34,050
I must say,
I had no idea I was this famous.

198
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:35,960
Don't let it get to you.

199
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:38,760
Some people just love to gossip.

200
00:16:40,490 --> 00:16:43,360
By the way, the lady who came in after us.

201
00:16:43,530 --> 00:16:45,700
She works at our complex as a helper.

202
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,430
Do you know her?

203
00:16:47,970 --> 00:16:50,540
No, I don't.

204
00:16:51,170 --> 00:16:52,770
Really? I see.

205
00:17:04,619 --> 00:17:07,619
So? You're really going to kick them out?

206
00:17:07,690 --> 00:17:09,760
We have to deal with them
before the semester is over.

207
00:17:10,060 --> 00:17:11,859
The autumn break is coming up.

208
00:17:13,190 --> 00:17:16,300
Still, she used to be a hotshot lawyer.

209
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,900
She won't obediently say yes
and just leave.

210
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:21,740
Then what? Should we just leave her be?

211
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:25,109
No. It's just that
all the moms here including you

212
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:26,940
don't enjoy making a fuss.

213
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:30,210
Why are you so serious?

214
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:32,210
We decide our standard of living.

215
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:34,480
This is a paradise for the kids,

216
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:37,450
but none of the moms here
want the kids to just play and not study.

217
00:17:37,690 --> 00:17:38,820
That's right.

218
00:17:38,890 --> 00:17:42,290
When it comes to private education,
we beat the moms in Gangnam.

219
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:44,060
We're way more serious about it
than they are.

220
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:45,660
You should think about it too.

221
00:17:45,830 --> 00:17:49,360
I refuse to let Jun-hee
be near a kid like that.

222
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:54,440
Of course. We're on your side, Ji-seon.

223
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:55,940
Yes.

224
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,340
She's just a lawyer with no connections.

225
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:02,240
What can she do on her own?

226
00:18:02,310 --> 00:18:03,510
Yes, that's right.

227
00:18:03,580 --> 00:18:06,450
The PTA parents of our school
are very powerful.

228
00:18:07,450 --> 00:18:09,250
Yes. Powerful, indeed.

229
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:11,690
So? What are you going to do?

230
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:14,660
I don't know if you've heard about it.

231
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:18,130
Our school expects us
to live up to a certain standard.

232
00:18:20,730 --> 00:18:22,360
"Code of Decency."

233
00:18:22,630 --> 00:18:25,100
If any HSC student or parent's conduct

234
00:18:25,170 --> 00:18:27,270
seriously harms the school's reputation,

235
00:18:27,330 --> 00:18:29,400
the foundation and the PTA
can have them expelled

236
00:18:29,470 --> 00:18:33,270
even if it's something that is not defined
by school regulations.

237
00:18:33,710 --> 00:18:35,410
What? Code of what?

238
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:36,610
There's such a thing?

239
00:18:37,380 --> 00:18:40,680
Does that mean we can make her leave?

240
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:44,990
It'll come into effect
if over 50 percent of the members say yes.

241
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:48,020
For that to happen, we must persuade
the other moms to sign a petition.

242
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:51,990
You never let us down.
You have a plan for everything.

243
00:18:52,130 --> 00:18:53,390
The thing is,

244
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:58,030
that means someone has to go around
with the petition.

245
00:18:58,100 --> 00:19:00,900
Don't worry.
I won't make any of you do it.

246
00:19:02,140 --> 00:19:06,310
To be honest, it would look bad on you
if we were involved.

247
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:09,010
Let's stop talking about this.
The kids will be out soon.

248
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:10,740
We need to de-stress before they're out.

249
00:19:10,810 --> 00:19:13,380
-Okay.
-I've been so stressed out.

250
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:16,320
My gosh. This is so nice.

251
00:19:24,460 --> 00:19:25,560
Thank you.

252
00:19:44,110 --> 00:19:45,110
[Information]

253
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:48,350
Let's go.

254
00:19:51,390 --> 00:19:52,790
What's wrong, Do-yeong?

255
00:19:52,850 --> 00:19:54,860
What? What do you mean?

256
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:58,490
Well, you look like you just saw

257
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:00,930
your husband with another woman.

258
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,560
No. Don't be silly.

259
00:20:03,930 --> 00:20:06,200
I think I was in the sauna for too long.

260
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:07,900
I feel a little dizzy.

261
00:20:18,910 --> 00:20:20,480
My gosh!

262
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:24,990
Mom, what did you do while I was gone?

263
00:20:25,050 --> 00:20:26,250
Weren't you bored?

264
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:29,360
I had a total blast with Jae-in's mom.

265
00:20:31,290 --> 00:20:33,530
-Good morning.
-Mr. Oh.

266
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:35,860
How was your day yesterday?

267
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:37,800
You must've had a tough time
with the kids.

