00:31:45,370 --> 00:31:46,570
Just one.

409
00:31:48,200 --> 00:31:50,100
Do you ever think about Dad?

410
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:53,310
No.

411
00:31:54,340 --> 00:31:56,740
I never think about him anymore.

412
00:31:58,480 --> 00:32:00,910
Come here. Give Mommy a hug.

413
00:32:06,750 --> 00:32:07,850
You are

414
00:32:08,790 --> 00:32:10,490
all I need.

415
00:32:11,260 --> 00:32:13,190
I can tell you drank more than one glass.

416
00:32:14,060 --> 00:32:15,190
By the way,

417
00:32:16,230 --> 00:32:18,430
Yi-chan had pictures of Dad.

418
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:19,630
And his phone.

419
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:21,330
-Really?
-Yes.

420
00:32:21,940 --> 00:32:24,570
There were pictures of you and me
on that phone.

421
00:32:25,270 --> 00:32:26,870
Where is it now?

422
00:32:26,940 --> 00:32:28,270
I don't know. It disappeared.

423
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:30,180
-It disappeared?
-Yes.

424
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,640
Did you tell Yi-chan?

425
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:37,820
Anyway, Mom.
Does that make Dad Yi-chan's dad too?

426
00:32:40,050 --> 00:32:42,620
Yi-chan was born in June,

427
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,760
and I was born in April.

428
00:32:46,430 --> 00:32:47,590
Is he my little brother?

429
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:50,700
Then what about Yi-chan's mom?

430
00:32:52,270 --> 00:32:53,330
Mom?

431
00:32:54,070 --> 00:32:56,200
Well, later.

432
00:32:56,570 --> 00:32:58,710
I'll explain everything later.

433
00:32:59,210 --> 00:33:02,040
But let's keep this between us for now.

434
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:04,240
Don't tell Yi-chan just yet.

435
00:33:04,310 --> 00:33:05,610
Why not?

436
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:08,980
Well...

437
00:33:12,320 --> 00:33:13,920
Think of it as a little game.

438
00:33:14,550 --> 00:33:17,160
We'll keep it a secret for now

439
00:33:17,320 --> 00:33:19,760
and tell Yi-chan and his mom later

440
00:33:20,460 --> 00:33:23,300
to surprise them. Wouldn't it be so fun?

441
00:33:24,160 --> 00:33:26,670
Okay. It'll stay between us.

442
00:33:42,680 --> 00:33:47,850
[History]

443
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:52,930
Hey, Jae-in.

444
00:33:52,990 --> 00:33:56,200
By any chance, did you see my phone
at Camp Day?

445
00:33:56,730 --> 00:33:57,900
What?

446
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:00,170
I don't think so.

447
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:01,800
Why?

448
00:34:02,270 --> 00:34:03,300
Really?

449
00:34:04,270 --> 00:34:05,410
It's nothing.

450
00:34:09,780 --> 00:34:10,909
What are you reading?

451
00:34:11,610 --> 00:34:12,980
Let me see.

452
00:34:17,520 --> 00:34:20,250
Why don't we have dinner together?
I have to stop by the market too.

453
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:22,489
Sounds good.

454
00:34:24,790 --> 00:34:26,030
Excuse me.

455
00:34:26,889 --> 00:34:28,060
Hi, it's me.

456
00:34:30,659 --> 00:34:31,960
Then I'll see you there.

457
00:34:32,230 --> 00:34:33,969
I'm at the school. I'll be right there.

458
00:34:34,699 --> 00:34:35,840
Okay.

459
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:41,370
Yeo-wool, I'm sorry.
Something came up at the gallery.

460
00:34:41,440 --> 00:34:42,739
No worries. You should go.

461
00:34:42,810 --> 00:34:44,340
-Let's have dinner together soon.
-Okay.

462
00:34:46,949 --> 00:34:48,050
-See you.
-Bye, Jae-in.

463
00:34:48,179 --> 00:34:50,179
Bye, Ms. Song.

464
00:34:55,350 --> 00:34:56,690
-Let's go.
-Okay.

465
00:35:04,430 --> 00:35:06,870
Can we see many stars there?

466
00:35:07,100 --> 00:35:08,530
Yes, I promise.

467
00:35:08,770 --> 00:35:10,300
It's a place called oreum.

468
00:35:10,640 --> 00:35:14,440
When you go up there,
you'll see a sky full of stars.

469
00:35:21,280 --> 00:35:23,150
Hello, Chairman Doh.

470
00:35:23,980 --> 00:35:25,320
Is everything okay?

471
00:35:26,250 --> 00:35:27,550
Yi-chan...

472
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,720
Sorry?

473
00:35:31,790 --> 00:35:33,390
What do you mean?

474
00:35:36,060 --> 00:35:37,900
A petition for expulsion?

475
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:39,330
[I mean just what I said.]

476
00:35:39,530 --> 00:35:43,200
The parent representatives
called an emergency PTA meeting.

477
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:47,840
As the chairman, I'd hate to see Yi-chan
leave the school this way.

478
00:35:48,540 --> 00:35:51,980
[But we'll need a solution
everyone can agree on.]

479
00:35:52,250 --> 00:35:55,250
This is all I can say for now.

480
00:35:55,880 --> 00:35:56,950
Okay.

481
00:36:04,490 --> 00:36:07,760
Then what's going to happen to Ms. Song?

482
00:36:07,830 --> 00:36:10,660
We'll have to wait and see.

483
00:36:14,500 --> 00:36:16,240
Couldn't we just let it pass?

484
00:36:16,470 --> 00:36:19,410
Let sleeping dogs lie.
Nothing's come of it.

485
00:36:19,470 --> 00:36:20,710
We don't know about that.

486
00:36:21,070 --> 00:36:24,810
I don't believe An Ji-yong
would've taken the fall for everyone.

487
00:36:27,750 --> 00:36:29,680
Any word from the surveillance team?

488
00:36:30,250 --> 00:36:31,720
We'll hear from them soon.

489
00:36:32,820 --> 00:36:35,990
If Song Yeo-wool knows something,
we'll have to find a way

490
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:37,520
to get everything back.

491
00:36:37,620 --> 00:36:39,560
If not...

492
00:36:39,630 --> 00:36:43,130
Then we won't get
any of the charity loss back.

493
00:36:43,460 --> 00:36:46,430
And the board will have to act quickly.

494
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:52,640
But you mustn't feel too bad.

495
00:36:52,910 --> 00:36:56,380
You know, stress ages you.

496
00:36:58,010 --> 00:36:59,150
Anyway,

497
00:37:00,350 --> 00:37:02,780
it's not like there's no way out

498
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:05,990
even if Song Yeo-wool is not around.

499
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:08,620
Meaning?

500
00:37:11,590 --> 00:37:15,330
You just have to get Hong Kong to invest.

501
00:37:16,060 --> 00:37:18,830
I told you. Over my dead body.

502
00:37:18,900 --> 00:37:21,200
Okay, okay. Got it.

503
00:37:39,490 --> 00:37:40,490
Oh, my.

504
00:37:45,690 --> 00:37:47,230
Mom, what's wrong?

505
00:37:47,290 --> 00:37:49,560
Yi-chan, stay in the car.

506
00:37:57,370 --> 00:37:59,040
Excuse me. Are you okay?

507
00:38:03,010 --> 00:38:04,040
Excuse me.

508
00:38:04,780 --> 00:38:06,580
Oh, ma'am. My goodness.

509
00:38:07,010 --> 00:38:08,080
Are you okay?

510
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:11,420
What happened? Oh, no.

511
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:13,490
Can you move?

512
00:38:13,650 --> 00:38:14,750
Let me see.

513
00:38:18,660 --> 00:38:21,460
Luckily, it's just a hairline fracture.

514
00:38:21,560 --> 00:38:23,530
No concussion or anything.

515
00:38:23,860 --> 00:38:27,070
Still, you had a car accident.
I think you should get some more tests.

516
00:38:27,130 --> 00:38:29,300
No, that's unnecessary.

517
00:38:29,940 --> 00:38:31,340
I'm fine.

518
00:38:32,570 --> 00:38:35,040
Then at least contact your family.

519
00:38:35,110 --> 00:38:36,980
I have no one to contact.

520
00:38:37,240 --> 00:38:38,440
Contact my family? No way.

521
00:38:41,350 --> 00:38:44,180
I've reported to the police
that you had a hit-and-run accident.

522
00:38:44,250 --> 00:38:45,750
They'll start the investigation
right away.

523
00:38:45,890 --> 00:38:48,960
I'll accompany you to the police station
once you've calmed down.

524
00:38:49,090 --> 00:38:51,690
-I'll stay here with you.
-No, you don't have to.

525
00:38:52,430 --> 00:38:53,660
I'm really fine.

526
00:38:54,030 --> 00:38:55,060
Yi-chan.

527
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:57,100
-Ms. Hwang.
-What happened?

528
00:38:57,160 --> 00:38:58,230
Are you hurt?

529
00:38:59,930 --> 00:39:01,630
Not me.

530
00:39:08,940 --> 00:39:14,710
[Blood Collection Room]

531
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:12,780
She had a hit-and-run accident.

532
00:39:13,210 --> 00:39:15,380
You saw her at the restaurant
the other day, right?

533
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:17,920
I'm going to accompany her
to the police station and help out.

534
00:39:18,020 --> 00:39:20,250
I see. Then don't worry
and go back inside.

535
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:21,820
I'll take Yi-chan to my place.

536
00:39:22,250 --> 00:39:24,120
Thank you. You're the best.

537
00:39:24,620 --> 00:39:28,130
Yi-chan, we'll have to go see the stars
some other time.

538
00:39:28,190 --> 00:39:29,900
Play at Jae-in's tonight.

539
00:39:30,030 --> 00:39:31,900
-I'll pick you up later.
-Okay.

540
00:39:32,830 --> 00:39:34,400
-Thanks.
-See you.

541
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:47,550
What?

542
00:39:48,380 --> 00:39:51,550
[Emergency Medical Center]

543
00:39:51,650 --> 00:39:53,250
[Emergency Care Center]

544
00:39:53,420 --> 00:39:56,790
Ma'am, you can't leave like this.

545
00:39:56,990 --> 00:39:58,620
-Let me take you to...
-I'm fine.

546
00:39:58,790 --> 00:40:01,990
-Still...
-The police are busy enough as it is.

547
00:40:02,060 --> 00:40:04,860
I don't want to bother them
with this trivial matter.

548
00:40:04,960 --> 00:40:07,000
It was an immature brat's doing anyway.

549
00:40:07,700 --> 00:40:11,770
Hold on. What do you mean
it was an immature brat's doing?

550
00:40:11,900 --> 00:40:15,810
-Do you know who did it?
-No, I don't know. I'm fine.

551
00:40:19,710 --> 00:40:20,980
[HSC International School
Lee Jun-mo]

552
00:40:22,780 --> 00:40:24,120
[HSC International School
Lee Jun-mo]

553
00:40:23,180 --> 00:40:24,480
What's with this name tag?

554
00:40:27,350 --> 00:40:29,060
Is this the person
who caused the accident?

555
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:31,590
Was the driver a student?

556
00:40:31,860 --> 00:40:33,030
My gosh.

557
00:40:34,260 --> 00:40:36,700
Ma'am, this is a hit-and-run by a minor.

558
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:38,630
You can't just let things slide.

559
00:40:38,860 --> 00:40:39,930
I'll help you so--

560
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:42,100
You don't need to! I don't need your help!

561
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:44,640
Don't make a big deal out of this.

562
00:40:49,810 --> 00:40:53,080
[HSC International School
Lee Jun-mo]

563
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:53,310
Lee Jun-mo.

564
00:40:54,110 --> 00:40:55,980
That name rings a bell.

565
00:40:57,620 --> 00:40:59,750
[HSC International School
Lee Jun-mo]

566
00:41:07,730 --> 00:41:10,700
[Please check your email for additional
personal information on CEO Nam Ji-seon.]

567
00:41:07,860 --> 00:41:09,860
[Oh]

568
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:18,370
"Owner of Seogwipo Locanda Jeju."

569
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:20,940
"After divorcing her husband
due to his affair eight years ago,"

570
00:41:21,010 --> 00:41:22,740
"she met her current husband,
Lee Jung-woo."

571
00:41:22,810 --> 00:41:24,080
"Her current husband, Lee Jung-woo,"

572
00:41:24,140 --> 00:41:27,450
"is the director of Eos Plastic Surgery
in Cheongdam-dong and Seogwipo."

573
00:41:25,010 --> 00:41:26,950
[Significant Remarks]

574
00:41:28,110 --> 00:41:30,180
So the kids' fathers are different.

575
00:41:30,250 --> 00:41:34,020
[Significant Remarks]

576
00:41:30,720 --> 00:41:31,920
"Son Lee Jun-mo"

577
00:41:31,980 --> 00:41:35,590
"quit school before getting expelled"

578
00:41:35,650 --> 00:41:37,260
"from Taft School in Connecticut in 2020."

579
00:41:37,990 --> 00:41:39,090
Lee Jun-mo?

580
00:41:42,660 --> 00:41:44,060
[HSC International School
Lee Jun-mo]

581
00:41:46,500 --> 00:41:48,130
Don't tell me it's her son?

582
00:42:24,170 --> 00:42:28,240
[Petition for Expulsion
Under the Code of Decency]

583
00:42:39,120 --> 00:42:40,150
Here.

584
00:42:40,950 --> 00:42:43,020
Here. What are you going to fold?

585
00:42:43,420 --> 00:42:44,990
Me? A paper airplane.

586
00:42:45,060 --> 00:42:46,690
Do you know how to fold an airplane?

587
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:48,860
-Teach me.
-Sure.

588
00:42:49,630 --> 00:42:50,860
Do what I do.

589
00:42:50,930 --> 00:42:52,970
Fold it in half lengthwise first.

590
00:42:53,570 --> 00:42:55,770
[Petition for Expulsion
Under the Code of Decency]

591
00:42:54,030 --> 00:42:55,000
Like this.

592
00:42:55,130 --> 00:42:58,300
I remember this part but forgot the rest.

593
00:43:00,810 --> 00:43:01,910
And then...

594
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:05,440
[Petition for Expulsion
Under the Code of Decency]

595
00:43:02,910 --> 00:43:04,210
Open this up.

596
00:43:04,410 --> 00:43:06,310
Then fold the bottom part.

597
00:43:07,050 --> 00:43:10,480
[Park Noah
Bang Young-ju]

598
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:09,350
Fold it

599
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:10,720
into a triangle.

600
00:43:10,780 --> 00:43:12,750
Do I do the same on the other side?

601
00:43:12,820 --> 00:43:13,850
Yes.

602
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:16,660
[Petition for Expulsion
Under the Code of Decency]

603
00:43:14,320 --> 00:43:15,820
Then fold it in half.

604
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:18,820
There. Let's eat.

605
00:43:22,660 --> 00:43:26,170
Wow. Did you make all of these?

606
00:43:27,030 --> 00:43:29,070
I wasn't sure what you'd like

607
00:43:29,130 --> 00:43:30,870
so I made this and that.

608
00:43:32,340 --> 00:43:33,470
Eat up.

609
00:43:34,370 --> 00:43:36,180
You too, Jae-in. Dig in.

610
00:43:45,020 --> 00:43:46,820
What's wrong? Is it weird?

611
00:43:49,790 --> 00:43:50,990
Is it too salty?

612
00:43:54,430 --> 00:43:56,530
No, it's super good!

613
00:43:59,370 --> 00:44:01,430
-My mom's cooking is amazing, right?
-Totally.

614
00:44:01,930 --> 00:44:04,070
My mom's cooking tastes like makeup.

615
00:44:05,340 --> 00:44:09,010
Dad always told mom her cooking was good
but left a bunch of food.

616
00:44:10,040 --> 00:44:12,850
Oh, he did?

617
00:44:14,410 --> 00:44:16,650
You look a lot like your dad, Yi-chan.

618
00:44:16,880 --> 00:44:19,950
Yes. Everyone said
I'm the spitting image of him.

619
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:24,760
You know...

620
00:44:25,760 --> 00:44:27,190
If you stay with me,

621
00:44:27,260 --> 00:44:30,260
you'll be able to eat my food every day
as much as you want.

622
00:44:30,330 --> 00:44:33,000
Would you like to live with me and Jae-in?

623
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:41,010
No. That's a bit...

624
00:44:43,380 --> 00:44:46,050
You're the first man
not to fall for my food, Yi-chan.

625
00:44:48,950 --> 00:44:52,150
You know, actually your dad...

626
00:44:52,220 --> 00:44:54,090
All right. No more talking.

627
00:44:54,620 --> 00:44:56,260
Let's eat before the food gets cold.

628
00:45:01,590 --> 00:45:03,500
-It's good.
-Is it?

629
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:18,180
Are you drinking alone?

630
00:45:18,710 --> 00:45:20,110
Why didn't you ask me to join?

631
00:45:20,180 --> 00:45:21,950
I saw you were reading.

632
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:24,080
I had the evening off today.

633
00:45:24,150 --> 00:45:27,250
I was reading
and didn't realize how late it was.

634
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:30,890
-Would you like a glass?
-Yes.

635
00:45:49,710 --> 00:45:51,810
Next week is the anniversary
of my uncle's death.

636
00:45:52,680 --> 00:45:54,450
I'll need to visit Seoul.

637
00:45:54,510 --> 00:45:56,780
How about I go with you?

638
00:45:57,120 --> 00:45:59,020
It's a family affair after all.

639
00:46:01,190 --> 00:46:03,120
You don't need to.

640
00:46:03,420 --> 00:46:04,860
It's my family's affair.

641
00:46:05,790 --> 00:46:08,160
Meeting my mom will be awkward

642
00:46:08,230 --> 00:46:10,800
and the round trip will tire you out.

643
00:46:11,700 --> 00:46:12,830
Well...

644
00:46:13,770 --> 00:46:16,600
I've got nothing to do
besides seeing patients.

645
00:46:19,140 --> 00:46:20,940
Does anything besides that matter?

646
00:46:21,670 --> 00:46:24,110
Seeing you only on the weekends
is hard enough.

647
00:46:28,010 --> 00:46:31,680
You're doing everything perfectly well.

648
00:46:36,520 --> 00:46:37,960
How about tonight?

649
00:46:38,020 --> 00:46:39,020
What?

650
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:41,560
Right.

651
00:46:42,690 --> 00:46:43,900
What about the kids?

652
00:46:45,860 --> 00:46:48,630
Jun-hee fell asleep a while ago
and Jun-mo isn't back yet.

653
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:53,040
Do you want to go upstairs first?

654
00:46:55,570 --> 00:46:58,410
I'm not feeling well today.

655
00:46:58,810 --> 00:47:00,950
You must be tired
after playing golf in the morning.

656
00:47:01,010 --> 00:47:02,350
Get some rest.

657
00:47:05,250 --> 00:47:08,450
Come later. I'm going to finish up
the book I was reading in the study first.

658
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:25,000
Ms. Nam,
I think you should quickly come outside.

659
00:47:35,150 --> 00:47:37,620
Jun-mo. Why aren't you coming inside?

660
00:47:41,390 --> 00:47:43,190
What's wrong?

661
00:47:43,260 --> 00:47:46,260
Mom, I think I killed someone.

662
00:47:46,790 --> 00:47:48,190
What should I do?

663
00:47:49,190 --> 00:47:52,400
What do you mean?
Tell me so I can understand.

664
00:48:51,060 --> 00:48:57,260
[Gate]

665
00:49:26,120 --> 00:49:27,230
Bingo.

666
00:49:28,690 --> 00:49:30,130
There, hold on.

667
00:49:34,370 --> 00:49:36,200
This is for you, Mom. I folded it myself.

668
00:49:36,470 --> 00:49:39,100
Nice. Are you giving me an airplane?

669
00:49:39,300 --> 00:49:40,440
Thank you.

670
00:49:42,840 --> 00:49:45,110
He can sleep over and go home tomorrow.

671
00:49:45,310 --> 00:49:47,980
It's okay. He should sleep at home.

672
00:49:48,110 --> 00:49:51,780
Thanks so much for today.
It must've been hard with two kids.

673
00:49:51,850 --> 00:49:52,920
Not at all.

674
00:49:53,590 --> 00:49:57,160
Right. What happened with that lady?
Did it go well?

675
00:49:58,090 --> 00:49:59,860
Well, I'm just going to leave it for now.

676
00:50:00,230 --> 00:50:03,430
She absolutely refuses to report it.

677
00:50:03,760 --> 00:50:04,830
Really?

678
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:06,600
Then what now?

679
00:50:06,730 --> 00:50:09,740
I don't know.
I guess I'll have to find another way.

680
00:50:11,440 --> 00:50:13,870
I should really get going.
I'll see you tomorrow.

681
00:50:13,940 --> 00:50:15,040
-Okay.
-Bye.

682
00:50:28,790 --> 00:50:32,260
[Petition for Expulsion
Under the Code of Decency]

683
00:50:38,230 --> 00:50:40,900
Not bad. You're pretty good.

684
00:50:42,830 --> 00:50:44,240
This is just a small portion.

685
00:50:45,440 --> 00:50:47,040
I have the rest.

686
00:50:47,470 --> 00:50:51,280
What can you do for me
if I give you all of them?

687
00:50:51,340 --> 00:50:53,710
Why must I do something for you?

688
00:50:54,310 --> 00:50:57,020
Since I've shown you my sincerity,

689
00:50:57,220 --> 00:50:59,820
I don't need this.

690
00:51:00,150 --> 00:51:02,250
But you need it.

691
00:51:06,290 --> 00:51:08,860
Tell me. What do you want from me?

692
00:51:13,900 --> 00:51:16,170
What is it? I'm with a guest.

693
00:51:16,330 --> 00:51:19,000
I'm sorry, ma'am. But it's urgent.

694
00:51:19,570 --> 00:51:23,010
I didn't want to barge in like this.
Sorry about that.

695
00:51:23,210 --> 00:51:25,440
I told you to wait outside.

696
00:51:34,850 --> 00:51:35,990
Yes, ma'am.

697
00:51:52,570 --> 00:51:54,670
I thought
you'd at least have some manners.

698
00:51:54,740 --> 00:51:57,080
I can't believe you barged in like this.
What do you want?

699
00:51:57,140 --> 00:52:00,680
I'm in no state
to think about manners and etiquette.

700
00:52:02,850 --> 00:52:05,120
Between 5 and 6 p.m. yesterday,

701
00:52:05,420 --> 00:52:08,850
there was a hit-and-run accident
on 193-gil in Seogwang-ri, Andeok-myeon.

702
00:52:09,320 --> 00:52:11,120
The driver was your son, Jun-mo.

703
00:52:12,120 --> 00:52:13,860
The victim will take four weeks
to recover.

704
00:52:14,060 --> 00:52:16,500
Since Jun-mo is over the age of 14,

705
00:52:16,860 --> 00:52:20,600
he is no longer a minor
and will be charged.

706
00:52:22,930 --> 00:52:24,240
What are you talking about?

707
00:52:25,500 --> 00:52:26,840
A hit-and-run?

708
00:52:27,570 --> 00:52:29,310
Talk about jumping to conclusions.

709
00:52:29,780 --> 00:52:31,510
There was no police report...

710
00:52:34,650 --> 00:52:35,750
Of course.

711
00:52:36,580 --> 00:52:38,380
So you did know.

712
00:52:38,450 --> 00:52:41,850
Like you said, there's no police report
because the report was canceled.

713
00:52:42,090 --> 00:52:43,490
I'm the one who reported it.

714
00:52:53,230 --> 00:52:55,270
I'll return the file to you for now.

715
00:53:04,840 --> 00:53:05,910
Here.

716
00:53:06,480 --> 00:53:09,310
This student ID was found at the scene.
And...

717
00:53:07,950 --> 00:53:09,380
[HSC International School
Lee Jun-mo]

718
00:53:11,520 --> 00:53:13,890
This was also left at the scene
after the accident.

719
00:53:13,950 --> 00:53:15,220
It came from an electric kickboard.

720
00:53:15,290 --> 00:53:19,020
It looks like you strategically tried
to cover up the accident.

721
00:53:21,760 --> 00:53:25,060
What can you even prove
with this junk and the student card?

722
00:53:26,060 --> 00:53:27,400
You'd better drop it.

723
00:53:27,470 --> 00:53:31,040
Unless you want to be sued for defamation
and false accusations.

724
00:53:32,270 --> 00:53:35,810
I don't know.
I dug a little more into your son,

725
00:53:35,940 --> 00:53:37,910
-and I'm afraid I can't drop it.
-What?

726
00:53:38,710 --> 00:53:41,950
In 2020, he dropped out of the Taft School
in Connecticut

727
00:53:42,010 --> 00:53:43,680
immediately before he was expelled.

728
00:53:43,750 --> 00:53:45,080
The cause of expulsion was marijuana.

729
00:53:45,580 --> 00:53:48,550
Then he transferred to HSC
three months later.

730
00:53:49,050 --> 00:53:51,620
I must say, it is very impressive.

731
00:53:52,020 --> 00:53:55,430
That would've been impossible
without forging his student record.

732
00:53:52,920 --> 00:53:56,600
[Student record: Details about a student]

733
00:53:57,030 --> 00:53:59,160
I have no idea who told you such nonsense,

734
00:53:59,630 --> 00:54:02,030
but do you think this can change anything?

735
00:54:03,870 --> 00:54:06,840
If you keep messing with Yi-chan,
I'll have to do the same to you.

736
00:54:07,140 --> 00:54:09,110
As a parent of a student at this school,

737
00:54:09,170 --> 00:54:12,380
I can't condone a delinquent student
and a parent who covers up his crimes

738
00:54:12,440 --> 00:54:13,980
and substance abuse problem.

739
00:54:16,750 --> 00:54:18,420
A mere lawyer

740
00:54:19,180 --> 00:54:20,590
wants to blackmail me?

741
00:54:23,420 --> 00:54:27,190
Goodness.
I guess you still don't get it yet.

742
00:54:28,530 --> 00:54:31,160
Listen carefully, Ms. Nam.

743
00:54:31,230 --> 00:54:34,430
I have nothing more to lose.

744
00:54:34,700 --> 00:54:36,030
But you're different.

745
00:54:36,270 --> 00:54:38,840
What will happen to your kids
if this gets out?

746
00:54:39,100 --> 00:54:40,340
And what about the other moms?

747
00:54:40,510 --> 00:54:43,070
Does your new husband know
about all of this?

748
00:54:45,680 --> 00:54:47,850
You know, whether it's true or not
doesn't matter.

749
00:54:48,010 --> 00:54:51,680
Just seeing the rumor spread
will be entertaining enough.

750
00:54:53,550 --> 00:54:56,790
Anyway, I'm done talking.
I'm a busy lady too.

751
00:54:59,060 --> 00:55:00,590
I'm not done talking.

752
00:55:03,760 --> 00:55:04,830
About what?

753
00:55:05,200 --> 00:55:08,600
Why? Are you starting to get scared,
Ms. Nam?

754
00:55:08,670 --> 00:55:10,370
There's more than meets the eye.

755
00:55:10,600 --> 00:55:11,700
You see, Jun-mo

756
00:55:12,770 --> 00:55:14,770
is still deeply scarred by my divorce.

757
00:55:15,340 --> 00:55:18,010
You don't need to make all this fuss
over a kid's careless mistake.

758
00:55:19,380 --> 00:55:20,910
That poor boy is very lonely.

759
00:55:22,450 --> 00:55:25,080
Just a careless mistake
made by a lonely, pitiful kid.

760
00:55:25,520 --> 00:55:28,950
I'm moved by your desperate motherly love.

761
00:55:30,520 --> 00:55:32,120
Tell me what you want,

762
00:55:32,690 --> 00:55:34,760
but leave Jun-mo out of it.

763
00:55:35,030 --> 00:55:38,330
You're awfully confident.

764
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:40,670
For whom are you doing this?

765
00:55:40,730 --> 00:55:44,000
For your son?
Or for the sake of your own reputation?

766
00:55:52,510 --> 00:55:56,150
After discussing this matter
with the principal, teachers,

767
00:55:56,210 --> 00:55:57,220
and PTA members,

768
00:55:57,280 --> 00:55:58,980
I have concluded
as the chairman of the school

769
00:55:59,320 --> 00:56:02,920
that we cannot stay silent
and ignore these disgraceful events

770
00:56:03,120 --> 00:56:05,890
that may harm the school's dignity
and reputation

771
00:56:05,960 --> 00:56:09,030
and the uneasiness
they caused the parents.

772
00:56:10,360 --> 00:56:13,060
[Since many different actions
are required at this time,]

773
00:56:13,130 --> 00:56:15,200
[I'd like to take this time
to make a proposal.]

774
00:56:15,430 --> 00:56:19,400
[I suggest we bring in an expert who can
advise us on how we should go about]

775
00:56:19,500 --> 00:56:22,870
[handling rule violations
and all other occurrences at the school.]

776
00:56:47,770 --> 00:56:50,100
Ms. Song Yeo-wool, an attorney at law

777
00:56:50,200 --> 00:56:53,410
and mother of student, An Yi-chan.
Could you please stand up?

778
00:56:57,680 --> 00:57:01,280
To address and find solutions
to all of the aforementioned matters,

779
00:57:01,910 --> 00:57:05,220
we have decided to appoint Ms. Song
as the PTA's legal advisor.

780
00:57:13,360 --> 00:57:15,260
-What?
-What is going on?

781
00:57:25,940 --> 00:57:27,840
I am the president of the PTA,
Nam Ji-seon,

782
00:57:28,270 --> 00:57:31,040
and I nominated Ms. Song Yeo-wool.

783
00:57:35,780 --> 00:57:37,820
The parents have been in need of someone

784
00:57:37,880 --> 00:57:40,490
who could provide us with legal advice.

785
00:57:40,790 --> 00:57:44,860
We thank you for volunteering
even in a situation like this.

786
00:57:46,560 --> 00:57:47,690
I am Song Yeo-wool.

787
00:57:48,590 --> 00:57:52,160
I'm sure some of you are displeased
with me taking this position.

788
00:57:52,460 --> 00:57:55,700
But as a mother and for the sake
of the school and the students,

789
00:57:56,070 --> 00:57:58,800
I will stand on the side of the parents

790
00:57:58,870 --> 00:57:59,970
and do my best.

791
00:58:12,750 --> 00:58:15,320
If you want this buried quietly,

792
00:58:15,590 --> 00:58:17,820
answer my question honestly.

793
00:58:19,360 --> 00:58:21,660
CEO An Ji-yong of Midas Investment.

794
00:58:21,960 --> 00:58:23,090
I know you two were

795
00:58:23,630 --> 00:58:26,870
more than just CEO and investor.

796
00:58:28,070 --> 00:58:30,200
Tell me everything you know about him.

797
00:58:42,650 --> 00:58:43,920
An Ji-yong.

798
00:58:45,020 --> 00:58:47,050
He was well-known as an investment genius.

799
00:58:47,550 --> 00:58:49,020
As an aggressive investor,

800
00:58:49,090 --> 00:58:51,190
he specialized in
high-risk, high-return investments.

801
00:59:00,030 --> 00:59:02,300
After quitting his job
at a big securities company,

802
00:59:02,370 --> 00:59:04,340
he started his own company.
That's when he came to me.

803
00:59:04,400 --> 00:59:05,370
Why?

804
00:59:05,440 --> 00:59:07,770
He needed money to start taking risks.

805
00:59:08,670 --> 00:59:12,040
Considering the size of his company,
I thought it'd be safe.

806
00:59:12,240 --> 00:59:14,510
Then came the incident last year.

807
00:59:14,580 --> 00:59:17,120
I haven't been able to recover
all my losses yet.

808
00:59:19,550 --> 00:59:20,750
Is that it?

809
00:59:22,520 --> 00:59:23,590
What did you expect?

810
00:59:26,190 --> 00:59:28,760
Did you think I was fooling around
with your husband or something?

811
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:33,970
I'm disappointed.
Is that all you can think of?

812
00:59:36,000 --> 00:59:38,570
At first, I assumed you two had teamed up.

813
00:59:39,140 --> 00:59:40,610
You were married after all.

814
00:59:41,510 --> 00:59:43,610
So I couldn't let you

815
00:59:43,680 --> 00:59:46,080
show up and make a mess
at my kids' school.

816
00:59:46,910 --> 00:59:47,910
Is that...

817
00:59:49,180 --> 00:59:51,050
Is that why you've been harassing
me and my kid?

818
00:59:51,120 --> 00:59:52,520
The text, the flowers, and everything?

819
00:59:54,290 --> 00:59:56,920
You must be mistaken.

820
00:59:57,220 --> 00:59:59,260
Why would I get up to something
so childish?

821
01:00:00,190 --> 01:00:03,490
The flowers were sent
from the flower shop at your hotel.

822
01:00:03,560 --> 01:00:05,800
In that case, it must have been
the general affairs department.

823
01:00:06,400 --> 01:00:08,870
I can show you proof.

824
01:00:10,940 --> 01:00:12,500
Is that really all?

825
01:00:15,440 --> 01:00:18,240
You must want to pin
your husband's death on me.

826
01:00:18,610 --> 01:00:21,110
But I wouldn't sacrifice a person's life
for that kind of money.

827
01:00:22,980 --> 01:00:24,680
Does that answer your question?

828
01:00:27,990 --> 01:00:29,850
It's not over yet. Not for your son.

829
01:00:29,920 --> 01:00:33,290
Like I said, tell me what you want.

830
01:00:34,860 --> 01:00:38,500
What do you say?
How about you meet me halfway?

831
01:00:42,100 --> 01:00:44,100
Even if this concerns Jun-mo,

832
01:00:44,740 --> 01:00:47,070
my patience has a limit.

833
01:00:50,170 --> 01:00:52,510
I trust you'll be reasonable.

834
01:00:52,810 --> 01:00:54,480
A successful lawyer like you.

835
01:01:13,800 --> 01:01:20,340
[Oh Soon-sang]

836
01:01:14,800 --> 01:01:16,800
[Did you find what you were looking for?]

837
01:01:17,140 --> 01:01:21,010
[In an unfamiliar place,
beware of the one closest to you.]

838
01:01:43,190 --> 01:01:45,200
[Petition for Expulsion
Under the Code of Decency]

839
01:01:46,700 --> 01:01:48,700
[Student: Hwang Jae-in
Parent: Hwang Na-yoon]

840
01:01:49,600 --> 01:01:50,840
Hwang Na-yoon?

841
01:01:53,740 --> 01:01:55,610
Why is her name on...

842
01:02:34,050 --> 01:02:36,280
[Student: Hwang Jae-in
Parent: Hwang Na-yoon]

843
01:02:37,080 --> 01:02:38,180
Yeo-wool.

844
01:02:41,090 --> 01:02:42,090
Hey.

845
01:03:21,560 --> 01:03:23,460
Hey, I'm impressed.

846
01:03:23,760 --> 01:03:25,730
How did you make her change her mind?

847
01:03:26,400 --> 01:03:27,770
Well, I'm not sure.

848
01:04:00,900 --> 01:04:03,500
[High Class]

849
01:04:03,800 --> 01:04:05,640
[You still don't seem to understand]

850
01:04:05,700 --> 01:04:07,540
[why you should never trust
a person easily.]

851
01:04:07,610 --> 01:04:10,440
[The truth will come out eventually.]

852
01:04:10,510 --> 01:04:11,810
Let's just have fun.

853
01:04:12,180 --> 01:04:14,180
[Jae-in's mom came forward to help.]

854
01:04:14,250 --> 01:04:15,450
[I'm his big sister.]

855
01:04:15,510 --> 01:04:17,450
[Leave my little brother alone.]

856
01:04:17,520 --> 01:04:19,550
[He was with someone.]

857
01:04:19,620 --> 01:04:21,220
[A woman.]

858
01:04:21,290 --> 01:04:22,850
[Was it your doing all along?]

859
01:04:23,090 --> 01:04:24,360
[The incident at the reception,]

860
01:04:24,420 --> 01:04:26,260
[the text, the flowers, all of them?]

861
01:04:26,320 --> 01:04:28,390
[What makes you so sure
that you were first?]

862
01:04:28,630 --> 01:04:31,230
[I'm not the one who stole him. You did.]

